==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Springbuck
<hw>Spring"buck`</hw> <pr>(-b⟦ucr⟧k`)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[D. <ets>springbok</ets>; <ets>springen</ets> to spring, leap +
<ets>bok</ets> a he-goat, buck.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A South
African gazelle (<spn>Gazella euchore</spn>) noted for its graceful form
and swiftness, and for its peculiar habit of springing lightly and
suddenly into the air. It has a white dorsal stripe, expanding into a
broad patch of white on the rump and tail. Called also
<altname>springer</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>springboc</asp>, and <asp>springbock</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

